      "releaseNotes": {
        "releaseNotesTooltip": "<div><span class=\"tooltip-title\">What's new in JetPack 7.0 (rev.1):</span><ul><li>Based on Ubuntu 24.04 LTS and Kernel v6.8 LTS.</li><li>Support for NVIDIA Jetson AGX Thor Developer Kit and T5000 module.</li><li>OpenRM-based stack architecture.</li><li>Latest AI compute stack: CUDA 13, cuDNN 9.12, and TensorRT 10.13.</li><li>CoE [CSI over Ethernet ] support using Holoscan Sensor Bridge. Out-of-the-box experience with Eagle Camera Sensor Module LI-VB1940.</li><li>CSI/GMSL is supported via Argus whereas CoE is supported via SIPL Camera API.</li><li>NVIDIA optimized preemptable realtime kernel.</li><li>SBSA Architecture</li><li>Deepstream is now supported, you can select it from additional SDKs to install.</li></ul><a href=\"https://docs.nvidia.com/jetson/archives/r38.2/ReleaseNotes/Jetson_Linux_Release_Notes_r38.2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"tooltip-link\">Open Release Notes</a></div>",
